Quote: However, in our journeyings let us not forget that not very many years have elapsed since the best known of our many townships, now in telegraphic communication with the metropolis and with each other, and familiar in our mouths as "household words," were in the undisturbed possession of the swamp turkey and wood hen; and let us, in passing, record the leading improvements yearly effected in our rising upland towns, all of which we have known in their "day of small things."
