Quote: This great bag - 193 head was obtained by Messrs W. T. Hazlett, F. Double, J. Brey, and T. Withington, of Invercargill, in four days, and included four swans, 115 swamp turkeys, seven ducks, four pigs, one mountain sheep, one hare, 34 kakas, and 27 pigeons.
